						<summary>

						<p>Left door-jamb (lower portion) of the Mūlēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1183,</hi> expressed in chonogram <hi rend="italic">Guṇa-vasu-[tri-ṇayana],</hi> corresponding to 1261 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a gift of land by Jāyapanāyaka and Mantri Nāgaya for the maintenance of a lamp in the temple of God Sakalēśvaradēva.</p>						

						</summary>
